<item>
            <title>[MJAVADOC-85] &lt;taglet&gt; allow only one taglet</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/MJAVADOC-85</link>
                <project id="12317529" key="MJAVADOC">Maven Javadoc Plugin (Moved to GitHub Issues)</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The &lt;tt&gt;&amp;lt;taglet&amp;gt;&lt;/tt&gt; configuration element in the javadoc plugin allows for only one taglet, or doesn&apos;t document how to add more than one taglet.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;I tried to put one than one &lt;tt&gt;&amp;lt;taglet&amp;gt;&lt;/tt&gt; element in the &lt;tt&gt;pom.xml&lt;/tt&gt; file, but the last one seems to override all the previous ones.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;I tried space, coma, : and ; as separator, without success.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;


&lt;p&gt;It should be possible to add an arbitrary amount of &lt;tt&gt;&amp;lt;taglet&amp;gt;&lt;/tt&gt; elements, and each of them should register a new taglet (through a new occurence of &lt;tt&gt;-taglet&lt;/tt&gt; argument given to the &lt;tt&gt;javadoc&lt;/tt&gt; command line I guess). I tested that multiple occurence of &lt;tt&gt;&amp;lt;taglet&amp;gt;&lt;/tt&gt; works as expected with Ant.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
